### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@phoneNumber = 254112310754
@bookingId = 68
@amount = 1

### 1. Initiate STK Push
# This triggers the "Enter PIN" prompt on the phone number provided.
# Ensure your server is running and your .env has valid M-Pesa credentials.
POST {{baseUrl}}/mpesa/stk-push
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": {{amount}},
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "bookingId": {{bookingId}}
}


### 2. Mock M-Pesa Success Callback
# Use this to test your 'mpesaCallbackHandler' logic locally.
# This simulates Safaricom telling your server the payment was SUCCESSFUL.
# Replace 'CheckoutRequestID' with the one returned from the STK Push above if testing full flow.
POST {{baseUrl}}/mpesa-callback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Body": {
    "stkCallback": {
      "MerchantRequestID": "29115-3462711-1",
      "CheckoutRequestID": "ws_CO_02042026_TEST_123",
      "ResultCode": 0,
      "ResultDesc": "The service request is processed successfully.",
      "CallbackMetadata": {
        "Item": [
          { "Name": "Amount", "Value": {{amount}} },
          { "Name": "MpesaReceiptNumber", "Value": "RDK2X3P4Z5" },
          { "Name": "TransactionDate", "Value": 20260402222528 },
          { "Name": "PhoneNumber", "Value": {{phoneNumber}} }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}


### 3. Mock M-Pesa Cancelled/Failed Callback
# Use this to test how your server handles a user cancelling the transaction.
# It should log the failure but NOT trigger a ticket email.
POST {{baseUrl}}/mpesa-callback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Body": {
    "stkCallback": {
      "MerchantRequestID": "29115-3462711-1",
      "CheckoutRequestID": "ws_CO_02042026_TEST_123",
      "ResultCode": 1032,
      "ResultDesc": "Request cancelled by user."
    }
  }
}